# URLs to skip when checking broken links
# One regex per line

# Localhost and private IPs (in case you use them as examples in articles)
^https?://localhost
^https?://127\.0\.0\.1
^https?://0\.0\.0\.0
^https?://192\.168\.
^https?://10\.
^https?://172\.(1[6-9]|2[0-9]|3[0-1])\.

# Sites that block bots (often false positives)
^https?://(www\.)?linkedin\.com
^https?://(www\.)?twitter\.com
^https?://(www\.)?x\.com

# Giscus / GitHub Discussions (redirects to login when not authenticated)
^https?://giscus\.app
